for story 1A

Created Azure Storage Account source module with 6 files (main.tf, variables.tf, outputs.tf, tags.tf, versions.tf, .gitignore, README.md)
Implemented storage account + blob container (1:1 mapping with AWS S3)
Naming transformation for Azure compliance (removes hyphens, truncates to 24 chars)
Tag validation matching AWS module patterns
Tested successfully with terraform plan - 3 resources to create






Completion Notes:
- Added blob versioning support (enable_versioning variable, default: true)
- Implemented HTTPS-only traffic enforcement (enable_https_traffic_only variable, default: true)
- Added minimum TLS version configuration (min_tls_version variable, default: TLS1_2)
- Configured soft delete for blobs and containers (soft_delete_retention_days, default: 7 days)
- Implemented Customer-Managed Key (CMK) encryption support via Azure Key Vault (enable_cmk_encryption, key_vault_key_id variables)
- Platform-Managed Key (PMK) encryption enabled by default (Azure default behavior)
- Added shared_access_key_enabled variable for Azure AD authentication option
- Added validation to ensure key_vault_key_id is valid format when CMK enabled
- Documented RBAC role assignment structure in comments (Azure equivalent of IAM bucket policies)
- Added compliance tags for security features (versioning, https_only, min_tls_version, soft_delete_days, encryption_type)
- Added security-related outputs (versioning_enabled, https_only_enabled, min_tls_version, soft_delete_retention_days, encryption_type, identity_principal_id)
